Block formatting:
- footnotes (are these used at all?)
- block quotes, i.e. bq
- block code, i.e. bc



Inline formatting:
- no implementation yet
- hyperlinks, eg. "This is a link(Link title)":/target
- images, eg. !This is a link(Link title)!:/target
- linked images
- acronyms
- span, eg. %(date) Jan 15, 1983%
- entities
- inline elements:
  - _emphasis_
  - __italic__
  - *strong*
  - **bold**
  - ??cite??
  - -deletions-
  - +insertions+
  - ^superscript^
  - ~subscript~
- ability to disable textile formatting, eg. ==notextile==


Lists:
- nested lists
- styling: #(simple) first item
  - should this affect <ul>/<ol> or just one <li>? Maybe two modifiers?
- block splitting is broken if line folding is turned off


Modifiers:
- Allow use of e.g. ((( and ))) declarations at the end of a modifier block.
  The number of parentheses translated to the number of ems to set padding-left
  and padding-right to, respectively.


Tables:
- no implementation yet


Lockdown:
- enable/disable class
- enable/disable id
- enable/disable style
- enable/disable headers
- enable/disable block quotes
- enable/disable images
- enable/disable inline markup except for emph and strong
- enable/disable hyperlinks
- enable/disable code
- enable/disable alignments
- enable/disable tables
- enable/disable ==raw html code==
